    sudo ip6tables -L -v -n

Step 3: Re-run the Qualys CIS scan
    - Log in to Qualys portal
    - Go to PA SCA module
    - Run a new compliance scan against this server
    - Compare results with the original scan to confirm improvement

Step 4: Document everything
    - Record the date and time each change was made
    - Record who made the change
    - Record the before and after state
    - Keep a change log for audit purposes

Step 5: Update the AIDE database after all legitimate changes are complete
    sudo aide --update
    sudo cp /var/lib/aide/aide.db.new /var/lib/aide/aide.db

Step 6: Schedule recurring Qualys scans
    - Set up weekly or monthly CIS scans in Qualys
    - Review results regularly
    - Address any new failures promptly

Step 7: Establish ongoing maintenance
    - Review and rotate logs regularly
    - Keep the system patched: sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade
    - Review new CIS benchmark versions when published
    - Review firewall rules periodically and remove unused rules


